A Japanese noodle soup with four main regional styles: shio (salt), shoyu (soy), miso, and tonkotsu (pork bone).  The broth is the heart of the dish — tonkotsu broths simmer for 12–18 hours to extract collagen from the bones.  Toppings: chashu pork, soft-boiled marinated egg, nori, spring onion.
